x4freetext: - Detector description
3.75 MV Van de Graaff Accelerator
pulse width is 0.7 ns, repetition rate 250 kHz,
average beam current 2.0  microAmp
Metallic Li target of about 1 mg/cm2
.Proton beam energy adjusted so to be 30 and 100 keV
above the reaction 7-Li(p,n)7-Be threshold 1.881 MeV
giving neutrons in energy ranges 3-100, 3-225 keV
experimental energy resolution 0.5 ns
.Standard sample Au-197, 15 mm diameter, 0.4 mm =
2.2475E-3 atoms/b thickness, weight 1.2990 gram,
enclosing aluminium canning 0.1849 g
.Lead sample 15 mm diameter, 1.9 mm = 5.7243E-3 atoms/b
thickness, weight 3.4933 gram, enclosing Al canning
0.1820 gram
.Graphite sample 15 mm diameter, 2.51 mm = 2.1688E-2
atoms/b thickness, 0.7644 gram weight, enclosing
aluminium canning 0.2136 g
.Empty aluminium canning 0.1810 gram
.Corrections were made for multiple scattering,
for isotopic impurities, for neutron self-absorption,
for undetected events, for signal/background ratio for
different neutron energies
Statistical model calculations
+ +  Compiled by S.M.     + +
Last checking has been done.
SD: In Subents 014 -019: EN-MEAN -> KT and
values were corrected. BIB update in all Subents.
ERR-ANALYS move to Subents 002 - 028. Ref. on report
was corrected (KFK- => FZKA-).
Averaged over
energy interval given in data section
.Absolute measurement
Flight path is 78.8 cm, resolution 1.2 ns/m
Karlsruhe 4Pi-Ba-F2 detector consisting of
42 hexagonal and pentagonal crystals forming
a spherical Ba-F2 shell of 15 cm thickness and 10 cm
inner radius. Resolution is 7% at 2.5 MeV gamma
energy, peak efficiency  90 % at 1 MeV
.Praseodymium oxide powder disk pressed to 14.9 mm
diameter pellets in alum canning with 0.2 mm thick
walls, its weight 0.2519 gram. Sample thickness is
4.2 mm = 5.6363 atoms/b
Data from Table V of PR/C,59,(2),1154
Total Error
Statistical error
Total systematic error includes:
Error due to flight path uncertainty
Error due to neutron flux normalization
Error due to undetected events
Error due to stoichiometry of sample
Error due to multiple scattering and self-
shielding in sample
SD: ERR-ANALYS update.

Namely - contribution I-1 at low energies 0 - 3 keV
is calculated in three different ways
.Contribution I-2 covers the range of present
experiment
.For part I-3 above 225 keV this energy range cross
sections were taken from Joint Evaluated File (JEF).
Data from Table VIII of PR/C,59,(2),1154  and
Tbl. 21 of FZKA-6104 (I-x, ERR-S, ERR-SYS).
Uncertainty of Maxwellian-averaged
cross-section
The uncertainty of 1.5% of the gold standard is not
included in the quoted uncertainty since it cancels
out in most applications of relevance for nuclear
astrophysics
Statistical error
The overall systematic uncertainties of the
Maxwellian averaged cross sections include the
uncertainties of the cross-section ratios and of the
extrapolated components, I-1 and I-3.
